<Author>GENEAD
<Content>Nice room great location Stayed at the Bostonian Oct 24 and 25th.Entrance on North St. is undergoing renovation but after being directed to the lobby we were greeted by extremely friendly front desk personnel. We were upgraded from a standard room to a superior room with a very nice bathroom with oval tub and a nice showerhead with a hand held shower wand as well. Also had an ironing board, iron, hairdryer and, unexpectedly, a one cup at a time coffee maker. However no ice machines- you have to order ice to be sent up to the rooms. Elevators were never a problem it seemed to be at our beck and call whenever we needed to go up or down. Didn't seem to be many people there though very quiet hotel. Some noise from the street but hardly heard any after 10:00pm. or so. Nice big screen tv but no on screen channel guide. After having a Time Warner interactive or even a non interactive guide I really missed seeing what was on each channel and when. Didn't spend much time in the room after going through Faneuil Hall (Pizza Regina rules)! Quincy market North End and Trolley tour with a free Harbor Cruise tour.Ate at Bertucci's (good Tortelli good pasta, pizza's looked great but didn't have any, great rolls and dipping sauce tho) first night right across from Quincy Market after drinking at the bar and it was a good meal at a reasonable price. very friendly too. Mother Anna's the next night in the North end after touring the sights on the North End and checking out all the restaurants which is easy to get to from the Hotel just walk over a block and up Hanover. A very easy and interesting walk through history and by most of the great restaurants . Bostonians like to call their city the hub of the universe and it surely is the roots of democracy here in the States. The North church as well as other churches and the Paul Revere mall with all the plaques commemorating the founding fathers and other Bostonians instrumental in routing the British and establishing our country was truely enlighting.Back to the hotel. Great bed great bedding down comforter including 5 pillows. It is nice having a room so close to everything so didn't have to carry stuff all over as we could go across the street to the room to get rid of the packages or for a quick nap before dinner and also to have a nice clean bathroom when we needed it . The flush of the toilet by the way was instantaeous- they use some kind of a power flush system. Right outside and going around the corner on weekends is the Haymarket fruits and vegetables at unbelievable prices. Parking is $40 dollars a day but I saved at least that much in not having to take a T,or taxi or parking everyday in a garage or on the street down town and after watching how close people park and how they bang their way out of the tight spots didn't have to worry about damage to my car. The location is perfect. Also I was quoted by Priceline at $215 a night for a standard room and with their guarantee of 100% refund of the difference if I found the room for a cheaper rate - found Expedia cheaper and was refunded 64.00 back so got the room for $183. That pretty much paid for parking!. All in all would go back to this hotel with its great location in a minute. Hope this helps. 
